  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Saturday morning, Sophia woke me up early to go with her to the traditional market before it gets too crowded.",
      "zh": "星期六早上，Sophia 一大早叫我起床，趁市場還不算太擁擠之前跟她一起去買菜。"
    },
    {
      "en": "She carries the same woven basket every single week, and she refuses to use a plastic bag if she can help it.",
      "zh": "她每個星期都提著同一個編織籃子，只要能不用塑膠袋就絕對不用。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Our first stop was the fruit stand, where she picked apples, bananas, and a whole pile of small strawberries.",
      "zh": "我們第一站是水果攤，她挑了蘋果、香蕉，還有一整堆小小的草莓。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The farmer at the stand said the strawberries were the freshest ones he had all week, and Sophia bought two boxes just in case.",
      "zh": "攤位上的農夫說這批草莓是他這星期最新鮮的，Sophia 乾脆買了兩盒以防萬一。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Next we walked to the vegetable stand, and Sophia bought potatoes, carrots, and a few tomatoes for tonight's soup.",
      "zh": "接著我們走到蔬菜攤，Sophia 買了馬鈴薯、紅蘿蔔，還有幾顆番茄要煮今晚的湯。"
    },
    {
      "en": "She held up each tomato and checked the color carefully before putting it in the basket, like she was judging a small competition.",
      "zh": "她把每一顆番茄拿起來仔細看顏色才放進籃子，好像在評一場小小的比賽一樣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "At the meat stand, she bought a small amount of chicken, some fish, and a little beef for a special weekend dinner.",
      "zh": "在肉攤，她買了一點雞肉、一些魚，還有一小份牛肉，要做一頓特別的週末晚餐。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The price of fish had gone up since last week, and Sophia complained about it to the seller, who just laughed and gave her a small discount anyway.",
      "zh": "魚的價格比上星期漲了，Sophia 跟老闆抱怨了一下，老闆只是笑一笑，還是給了她一點折扣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I asked how much everything cost so far, and Sophia said she stopped counting dollars a long time ago at the market.",
      "zh": "我問到目前為止全部花了多少錢，Sophia 說她在市場買東西早就不算錢了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "She did admit that a dozen eggs and a bag of rice were the two things she never lets the price bother her.",
      "zh": "但她承認一打雞蛋跟一袋米是唯二兩樣她從不在意價格的東西。"
    },
    {
      "en": "We also stopped by a small stand selling butter, cheese, and fresh milk from a nearby farm.",
      "zh": "我們還在一個小攤停下來，那裡賣附近農場產的奶油、起司跟新鮮牛奶。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The seller gave me a tiny cup of milk to taste for free, and it was much sweeter than the milk we usually buy at the store.",
      "zh": "老闆給我一小杯牛奶試喝，味道比我們平常在超商買的牛奶甜多了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "On the way home, Sophia bought a small bag of sugar and a bag of salt, saying the kitchen was almost out of both.",
      "zh": "回家的路上，Sophia 買了一小袋糖跟一小袋鹽，說廚房兩樣都快沒了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "She let me choose one sweet treat with my own pocket money, so I picked a warm lemon cookie from the bakery stand.",
      "zh": "她讓我用自己的零用錢挑一樣甜點，我挑了烘焙攤上一塊溫熱的檸檬餅乾。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The cookie cost less than a dollar, and it was still warm enough to melt a little in my hand.",
      "zh": "那塊餅乾不到一塊錢，而且還溫熱到會在我手裡稍微融化。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia bought herself a small cup of hot tea, and I had a cold juice to go with my cookie.",
      "zh": "Sophia 給自己買了一小杯熱茶，我則配著餅乾喝了一杯冰果汁。"
    },
    {
      "en": "By the time we finished, her basket was completely full, and my arms were tired just from carrying half of it.",
      "zh": "等我們逛完，她的籃子已經完全裝滿了，光是幫忙提一半我的手臂就已經很痠了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia said a good market trip should always end with something sweet, otherwise the whole morning was a waste.",
      "zh": "Sophia 說一趟成功的市場之旅最後一定要吃點甜的，不然整個早上就白費了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "When we got home, William ran straight for the strawberries before Sophia even had a chance to put down her basket.",
      "zh": "我們一到家，William 沒等 Sophia 把籃子放下就直接衝去搶草莓。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia told him to wash his hands first, and for once, he actually listened without a single complaint.",
      "zh": "Sophia 叫他先去洗手，這次難得他一句抱怨都沒有就乖乖照做了。"
    }
  ],
